Nigeria â€™s Federal High Court in the
commercial capital, Lagos, awarded 1.2 billion naira in damages
against GlaxoSmithKline Nigeria Plc and two of its units for
trademark infringement, the  Nation  said, citing Justice James
Tsoho.  The money was awarded to Continental Pharmaceuticals Ltd.,
which had argued that GlaxoSmithKline infringed its registered
trademark for the analgesic Conphamol, the Lagos-based newspaper
